Reasoning: The paper discusses a technical process for representing and reconstructing simplified polygons using a qualitative spatial calculus. This involves techniques related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for spatial reasoning, computer vision (cs.CV) for image processing, graphics (cs.GR) for polygon representation, machine learning (cs.LG) for pattern recognition, and robotics (cs.RO) for spatial navigation.
